  <mainDescription>The project charter must be clear and concise. This statement is meant to inform all proceeding requirements documents of
        the agreement between the project sponsor and the project team.&lt;br style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot; />
         The Project Charter should include:&lt;br />
         &lt;br style=&quot;font-family: Candara;&quot; />
         
        &lt;ul>
            &lt;li>
                Project scope or boundaries
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                Project purpose
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                Project objectives
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                High-level project description, requirements and risks
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                Summary budget and milestone schedule
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                Stakeholder list
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                Project approval requirements (what constitutes success, who decides it, who signs off)
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                Assigned project manager, responsibility, and authority level
            &lt;/li>
            &lt;li>
                Name and authority of the sponsor or other person(s) authorizing the project charter
            &lt;/li>
        &lt;/ul></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
